A PriorityQueue in Java is a queue where elements are ordered based on their priority, rather than the order of insertion. By default, it uses natural ordering (min-heap), but a custom comparator can be used to define different priorities.
a. Elements are processed based on priority rather than insertion order.
b. Supports standard queue operations like add(), poll(), and peek().
c. Automatically grows as elements are added and null insertion is not possible .
d. Uses a heap data structure internally to ensure efficient insertion and removal of the highest-priority element.

